Subject: =?UTF-8?q?slayzone:=20Phase=205.5=20focus=20chain=20=E2=80=94=20C?=
 =?UTF-8?q?md+1..9=20region=20focus=20accelerators?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SlayzoneBrowserView registers Cmd+1 through Cmd+9 as view-level
accelerators; AcceleratorPressed maps the key to the region slot at that
index in SlayzoneRegionContainer::kRegionIds and calls RequestFocus on the
underlying views::WebView. Upstream views::FocusManager already handles
cross-WebView Tab cycling; this adds the direct index-jump path.
Region-origin focus requests (region → Mojo → browser → slot) land in 5.6.
